tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE urban_green_spaces (
    park_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    park_name VARCHAR(255),
    park_size FLOAT,
    park_location VARCHAR(255),
    establishment_year INT
);

CREATE TABLE park_amenities (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    park_id INT NOT NULL,
    amenity_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (park_id) REFERENCES urban_green_spaces(id)
);

CREATE TABLE UrbanGreenSpaces (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    area DECIMAL(10, 2),
    location VARCHAR(255),
    established_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE ParkRelations (
    relation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    park_id INT,
    amenity_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (park_id) REFERENCES UrbanGreenSpaces(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (amenity_id) REFERENCES ParkAmenities(amenity_id)
);

CREATE TABLE UrbanGreenSpaces(
   green_space_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   green_space_name VARCHAR(255),
   area_acres DECIMAL(10, 2),
   city VARCHAR(100),
   location_lat DECIMAL(10, 6),
   location_long DECIMAL(10, 6)
)

CREATE TABLE ParkAmenities(
   amenity_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   amenity_name VARCHAR(255),
   category VARCHAR(50),
   green_space_id INT,
   FOREIGN KEY (green_space_id) REFERENCES UrbanGreenSpaces(green_space_id)
)

CREATE TABLE ParkUsers(
   user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   user_name VARCHAR(255),
   age INT,
   green_space_id INT,
   FOREIGN KEY (green_space_id) REFERENCES UrbanGreenSpaces(green_space_id)
)

CREATE TABLE ParkRatings(
   rating_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   user_id INT,
   rating DECIMAL(2, 1),
   review TEXT,
   FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES ParkUsers(user_id)
)

CREATE TABLE ParkEvents(
   event_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   event_name VARCHAR(255),
   event_date DATE,
   green_space_id INT,
   FOREIGN KEY (green_space_id) REFERENCES UrbanGreenSpaces(green_space_id)
)
